<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I am marking as major b/c ive seen this come up alot with the introduction of view renderer.</p>

<p>Sample Exception (taken from mailing list):</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
Fatal error: Uncaught exception 'Zend_View_Exception' with message 'script 'index/index.phtml' not found in path' in
&gt; E:\Localhost\DVDCollector\library\Zend\View\Abstract.php:853 Stack trace:
&gt; #0 E:\Localhost\DVDCollector\library\Zend\View\Abstract.php(764):
</code></pre>

<p>I think it would be a good idea to include the script stack (in the same fashion that require or include does) when an exception of this type is thrown.</p>

<p>I propose the output look like this:
assuming this script stack:
1. ./user/modules/blog/views/scripts/
2. ./user/templates/views/scripts/</p>

<p>script 'index/index.phtml' not found in path (./user/templates/views/scripts/:./user/modules/blog/views/scripts/)</p>

<p>separated by PATH_SEPARATOR.</p>

<p>Or something similar.</p>

<p>message me if this needs more clarification.</p>

